I know everything.

349
00:25:47.120 --> 00:25:50.080
- Where have you been?
- I thought you knew
everything.

350
00:25:51.160 --> 00:25:52.800
- [growling]
- Hey, Auntie K.

351
00:25:52.840 --> 00:25:54.800
You're looking
remarkably groomed today.

352
00:25:54.840 --> 00:25:56.640
- Hello, Terk.
- [roars]

353
00:25:56.680 --> 00:25:59.240
[Terk] Not the neck!
Not the neck there, T.

354
00:26:01.000 --> 00:26:03.680
[Terk] Watch it! Oh! Ow!

355
00:26:05.560 --> 00:26:09.160
Okay, it's all fun and games
till someone loses an eye.

356
00:26:09.240 --> 00:26:11.840
[Tantor] Please stop.
Somebody's gonna
get hurt here.

357
00:26:11.920 --> 00:26:14.480
- [Tantor] And it's always me.
- [Terk] Cramp in the calf.

358
00:26:14.560 --> 00:26:17.000
- Please!
- Okay. Okay, you win.

359
00:26:17.080 --> 00:26:21.520
Ow! Okay, okay, you win.
Hello! Down here.
Yo, yo! Let go!

360
00:26:21.600 --> 00:26:24.560
- Oh, sorry, Terk.
- What kind of animal are you?

361
00:26:24.640 --> 00:26:27.320
You know, I been thinking
lately that maybe Tarzan

362
00:26:27.360 --> 00:26:29.480
could be some
subspecies of elephant.

363
00:26:29.520 --> 00:26:31.520
[Terk] What are you, crazy?
An elephant?

364
00:26:31.600 --> 00:26:35.480
[Tantor] Listen to me.
Think about it. He enjoys
a peanut, I enjoy a peanut.

365
00:26:35.520 --> 00:26:37.360
He looks nothing like you.

366
00:26:37.440 --> 00:26:39.200
[roaring]

367
00:26:58.200 --> 00:27:00.080
[low growling]

368
00:27:05.240 --> 00:27:06.840
- [ferocious roar]
- Ahhhh!

369
00:27:13.480 --> 00:27:15.600
[apes screeching, hooting]

370
00:28:14.600 --> 00:28:16.120
[Tarzan yelps]

371
00:28:31.120 --> 00:28:33.600
[rustling]

372
00:28:34.520 --> 00:28:36.560
[grunting]

373
00:28:51.800 --> 00:28:54.040
[triumphant grunting]

374
00:29:03.680 --> 00:29:06.480
[Tarzan yells]

375
00:29:25.000 --> 00:29:27.800
[Terk] Okay everybody,
move aside. Outta my way.

376
00:29:27.840 --> 00:29:31.040
Best friend coming through.
That would be me.

377
00:29:31.040 --> 00:29:33.240
And you, don't make
a habit of that, okay?

378
00:29:33.320 --> 00:29:35.840
There are other ways
of getting attention.

379
00:29:35.920 --> 00:29:37.840
- I'll try to remember that.
- All right.

380
00:29:37.960 --> 00:29:41.120
I was right behind you
if you needed me.
I had you covered.

381
00:30:12.800 --> 00:30:15.040
[gunshot]

382
00:30:15.080 --> 00:30:17.200
[birds crying]

383
00:30:18.720 --> 00:30:20.240
What was that?

384
00:30:20.280 --> 00:30:23.040
I... It wasn't me, I swear.

385
00:30:23.080 --> 00:30:25.880
- [Tantor] Okay, maybe it was.
- [Kerchak] Everyone,

386
00:30:25.920 --> 00:30:27.680
let's move.

387
00:30:29.240 --> 00:30:31.440
[apes grunting]

388
00:30:31.520 --> 00:30:33.720
[gunshot]

389
00:30:45.880 --> 00:30:48.440
[sniffing]

390
00:31:10.640 --> 00:31:14.200
- [coughing, choking]
- [gunshot]

391
00:31:15.800 --> 00:31:19.320
[Clayton] I was reminded of a
safari I led up the Zambezi.

392
00:31:19.440 --> 00:31:23.520
Marvelous.
Lots of hunting, yes.
Bang, bang, bang, bang, bang.

393
00:31:23.600 --> 00:31:25.520
Wildebeest everywhere.

394
00:31:25.600 --> 00:31:30.800
Two bearers loading
three rifles for me,
blasting away.

395
00:31:30.880 --> 00:31:34.480
That's when I knew
I was born for Africa

396
00:31:34.560 --> 00:31:37.600
and Africa was created for...

397
00:31:39.600 --> 00:31:41.320
[gunshot]

398
00:31:45.840 --> 00:31:47.320
[Porter] Clayton?

399
00:31:47.360 --> 00:31:49.680
[panting] Clayton...
Oh, there you are.

400
00:31:49.680 --> 00:31:52.720
What is it?
What is it, Clayton?
Are we in danger?

401
00:31:52.800 --> 00:31:54.480
I thought I saw something.

402
00:31:54.560 --> 00:31:58.120
Is it a Hippopotamus
amphibious or
a Rhinoceros bihornus?

403
00:31:58.160 --> 00:31:59.760
[Clayton] Professor,
don't move!

404
00:31:59.840 --> 00:32:01.960
- Oh, right.
- [Jane] Daddy?

405
00:32:02.000 --> 00:32:04.240
Ow, ow, ow!

406
00:32:04.320 --> 00:32:07.720
Daddy, what's all
the hullabaloo about? [grunts]

407
00:32:08.640 --> 00:32:10.920
[Jane] Ow! Ah!

408
00:32:11.000 --> 00:32:12.360
What is it, Daddy?

409
00:32:12.440 --> 00:32:15.480
Mr. Clayton asked me not
to move. He saw something.

410
00:32:16.800 --> 00:32:18.560
Uh... Ooh!

411
00:32:18.640 --> 00:32:19.920
I moved.

412
00:32:20.000 --> 00:32:22.880
Uh, Mr. Clayton?
Sorry, excuse me.

413
00:32:22.960 --> 00:32:26.480
But my father and I came
on this expedition
to study gorillas,

414
00:32:26.520 --> 00:32:29.560
and I believe your shooting
might be scaring them off.

415
00:32:29.640 --> 00:32:32.040
You hired me to protect you,
Miss Porter,

416
00:32:32.120 --> 00:32:34.160
and protect you I shall.

417
00:32:34.200 --> 00:32:36.400
And you're doing
a marvelous job of it.

418
00:32:36.480 --> 00:32:37.720
But we only
have a short time

419
00:32:37.800 --> 00:32:40.200
before the ship returns,
you see...

420
00:32:40.280 --> 00:32:43.800
Jane! Jane, do you realize
what you're standing in?

421
00:32:43.880 --> 00:32:46.320
- A gorilla's nest!
- [gasps] Daddy!

422
00:32:46.400 --> 00:32:49.800
At last!
Our first sign in days.

423
00:32:49.880 --> 00:32:52.520
Do you think the beasts
could be nearby?

424
00:32:52.560 --> 00:32:54.720
Could be. Why, I mean,
there's the evidence.

425
00:32:54.760 --> 00:32:57.240
[Porter stammering] They
can't be very far, anyway.

426
00:32:57.320 --> 00:32:59.040
Look! Over there and there...

427
00:32:59.160 --> 00:33:00.760
[Porter] Where?
Yes, more nests!

428
00:33:00.840 --> 00:33:02.720
- I see them!
- Just as you predicted!

429
00:33:02.800 --> 00:33:04.360
Family groups!

430
00:33:04.400 --> 00:33:06.400
Oh, Jane, I love you.

431
00:33:06.440 --> 00:33:09.480
- [laughter]
- Family groups?

432
00:33:09.560 --> 00:33:12.320
[laughing] Excuse me,
but these are wild beasts

433
00:33:12.400 --> 00:33:15.240
that would sooner tear your
head off than look at you.

434
00:33:15.320 --> 00:33:16.400
On the contrary, Mr. Clayton.

435
00:33:16.480 --> 00:33:19.840
Daddy's theory is that
these are social creatures,
not monsters.

436
00:33:19.920 --> 00:33:22.080
[bird squawking]

437
00:33:24.600 --> 00:33:27.840
Mr. Clayton, please.
What if it's a gorilla?

438
00:33:27.920 --> 00:33:29.920
It's no gorilla.

439
00:33:32.440 --> 00:33:35.320
Mmm.
Perhaps we should press on.

440
00:33:35.400 --> 00:33:36.440
Yes, indeed.

441
00:33:36.480 --> 00:33:38.480
Now, we should keep
heading west,

442
00:33:38.560 --> 00:33:40.280
following
the Ganoderma ablonatum.

443
00:33:40.360 --> 00:33:42.120
[Clayton]
Excellent, professor.

444
00:33:42.200 --> 00:33:45.160
I could've used your expertise
on my last safari.

445
00:33:45.240 --> 00:33:47.120
I was in the mountainous
region of Zambia.

446
00:33:47.160 --> 00:33:50.440
- [cries out] Oh!
- [Clayton]
Yes, very dangerous.

447
00:33:50.480 --> 00:33:52.360
Oh!

448
00:33:52.440 --> 00:33:55.520
Are you what all
the fuss was about?

449
00:33:55.600 --> 00:33:58.520
[whispering] Daddy!
Daddy, quick!

450
00:33:58.640 --> 00:34:00.720
No, wait. Hold still.

451
00:34:00.800 --> 00:34:02.280
Oh, my good...

452
00:34:02.360 --> 00:34:07.120
You may not be a gorilla,
but you are
one sweet little...

453
00:34:11.880 --> 00:34:13.560
There you go.
What do you think?

454
00:34:15.080 --> 00:34:17.120
[squeals]

455
00:34:17.240 --> 00:34:19.680
What? Oh!

456
00:34:19.760 --> 00:34:21.400
[Jane] Why, you little...

457
00:34:21.480 --> 00:34:25.560
Well, this is
absolutely peachy.
Come to study gorillas

458
00:34:25.640 --> 00:34:29.160
and get my sketchbook
pinched by a baboon.

459
00:34:29.200 --> 00:34:31.720
[grunting, laughing]

460
00:34:36.480 --> 00:34:38.160
Give me that!

461
00:34:40.000 --> 00:34:41.600
Come on now, enough of this.

462
00:34:41.680 --> 00:34:43.640
I want this paper
on the count of three.

463
00:34:43.680 --> 00:34:45.280
One.

464
00:34:45.320 --> 00:34:47.160
Two.

465
00:34:47.200 --> 00:34:49.440
Oh, look, bananas!

466
00:34:49.520 --> 00:34:53.400
[laughing] I can't believe
you fell for that one.

467
00:34:53.480 --> 00:34:54.920
[crying]

468
00:34:55.000 --> 00:34:58.000
No, no, don't give me
those crocodile tears.

469
00:34:58.080 --> 00:34:59.840
What would your parents
have to say?

470
00:34:59.880 --> 00:35:01.120
- [roaring]
- [yelps]

471
00:35:04.400 --> 00:35:06.400
You see, I told you
they'd be cross.

472
00:35:06.480 --> 00:35:09.360
Go easy on him.
Children will be children.

473
00:35:29.200 --> 00:35:30.560
[Jane] I'm flying!

474
00:35:30.600 --> 00:35:34.120
What on earth am I...
[gasps, screams]

475
00:35:35.160 --> 00:35:37.840
[Jane] Get off! Get off!

476
00:35:42.720 --> 00:35:45.600
Put me down! Put me down!

477
00:35:45.680 --> 00:35:48.080
[Jane] No, pick me up,
pick me up!

478
00:35:52.560 --> 00:35:54.800
[Jane] Help!

479
00:35:54.880 --> 00:35:56.720
Oh, no!

480
00:35:56.800 --> 00:35:59.280
[Jane screaming]

481
00:36:09.840 --> 00:36:12.320
[laughing]

482
00:36:14.760 --> 00:36:17.080
Unhand me, monkey!

483
00:36:37.880 --> 00:36:39.120
Over there!

484
00:37:10.600 --> 00:37:13.120
[chattering]

485
00:37:14.320 --> 00:37:16.280
[chattering]

486
00:37:27.160 --> 00:37:28.840
[panting]

487
00:37:28.880 --> 00:37:32.320
I'm in a tree with a man
who talks to monkeys.

488
00:37:33.760 --> 00:37:35.360
I can't do this. I can't...

489
00:37:35.480 --> 00:37:38.120
Oh! This is good.
This is very good.

490
00:37:38.160 --> 00:37:40.320
I... Oh! Wait.

491
00:37:40.360 --> 00:37:43.600
One, two. [yelps]

492
00:37:45.440 --> 00:37:47.560
It can't get any worse,
can it?

493
00:37:47.640 --> 00:37:49.240
[thunder crashes]

494
00:37:51.040 --> 00:37:53.240
Obviously it can.

495
00:37:56.280 --> 00:37:57.360
[shrieks]

496
00:38:01.880 --> 00:38:04.720
Stay back. No, don't...
Don't come any closer.

497
00:38:04.800 --> 00:38:06.040
Please, don't.

498
00:38:06.080 --> 00:38:07.760
What are you...
What are you doing?

499
00:38:07.840 --> 00:38:12.080
[laughing] No, please don't.
That tickles.

500
00:38:12.160 --> 00:38:14.040
No, get off, get off.
Get off!

501
00:38:15.080 --> 00:38:16.640
[Jane] It serves you right.

502
00:38:16.720 --> 00:38:19.200
Stay away from me,
like a very good wild man.

503
00:38:19.280 --> 00:38:21.720
You stay. I'm warning you.

504
00:38:21.800 --> 00:38:23.680
My father won't
take kindly to you...

505
00:38:23.720 --> 00:38:27.000
No. That's...
Now, that's close enough.

506
00:38:27.040 --> 00:38:30.360
How dare you? What...?

