00:43:26.840 --> 00:43:29.200
♪ Bomp-bomp-bomp-bomp ♪

589
00:43:29.240 --> 00:43:30.880
[drums playing]

590
00:43:32.880 --> 00:43:34.680
[Terk] Yeah!

591
00:43:36.720 --> 00:43:41.240
[all] ♪ Shoo-bee-do-da-be-da
Do-be-do-da-ba-da-ba-do ♪

592
00:43:41.320 --> 00:43:44.560
♪ Shoo-bee-do-da-be-da
Do-be-do-da-ba-da-ba-do ♪

593
00:43:44.680 --> 00:43:46.640
♪ Wa-ba-ba-de-woo ♪

594
00:43:46.720 --> 00:43:49.040
[faint music]

595
00:43:49.120 --> 00:43:51.280
- [shattering]
- [Porter] Wha...?

596
00:43:51.360 --> 00:43:54.760
♪ Shoo-bop-she-doo ♪

597
00:43:55.960 --> 00:43:59.560
♪ Shoo-bop-she-doo ♪

598
00:43:59.600 --> 00:44:01.040
♪ Woo-woo! ♪

599
00:44:01.080 --> 00:44:04.160
[speeding up]
♪ Shoo-bop-she-doo ♪

600
00:44:05.520 --> 00:44:08.880
♪ Shoo-bop-she-doo ♪

601
00:44:08.960 --> 00:44:10.280
♪ Woo! ♪♪

602
00:44:10.360 --> 00:44:12.320
[trumpet trails off]

603
00:44:13.560 --> 00:44:16.360
[gasping] Gorillas!

604
00:44:18.640 --> 00:44:20.720
[grunting]

605
00:44:24.120 --> 00:44:26.040
He's one of them.

606
00:44:46.680 --> 00:44:47.800
[growl]

607
00:44:47.880 --> 00:44:50.960
- Oh, my...
- [roar]

608
00:44:54.120 --> 00:44:56.440
[Jane whimpering]

609
00:45:24.720 --> 00:45:28.200
[Porter and Clayton]
Jane!

610
00:45:30.600 --> 00:45:33.120
[Porter] Jane, where are you?

611
00:45:33.160 --> 00:45:35.480
Jane. Oh, Jane.

612
00:45:35.560 --> 00:45:37.960
- Thank goodness.
- Good heavens, what happened?

613
00:45:38.000 --> 00:45:40.320
Are you all right?
We've been everywhere.

614
00:45:40.400 --> 00:45:41.600
Oh, my goodness.

615
00:45:41.640 --> 00:45:45.480
- Daddy, I was out walking...
- Yes, yes.

616
00:45:45.520 --> 00:45:47.320
Little baby.
Little baby monkey.

617
00:45:47.360 --> 00:45:48.760
- I drew a picture.
- Go on.

618
00:45:48.840 --> 00:45:50.960
- The monkey starts crying.
- Poor baby.

619
00:45:51.000 --> 00:45:53.840
But I turned round, and
there's a whole fleet of them!

620
00:45:53.920 --> 00:45:55.560
- Of what?
- An army of monkeys!

621
00:45:55.640 --> 00:45:57.600
- A huge tree full of them...
- Monkeys?

622
00:45:57.680 --> 00:45:59.240
...screaming at me!

623
00:45:59.360 --> 00:46:02.120
Theropithecus baboonus.
She's very good at this.

624
00:46:02.160 --> 00:46:03.760
- Oh, really?
- Terrified, I was.

625
00:46:03.840 --> 00:46:07.240
Suddenly, I was swinging
in the vines, up in the air!

626
00:46:07.320 --> 00:46:08.960
- With the monkeys?
- Flying.

627
00:46:09.000 --> 00:46:11.200
- In the air.
- And I'm all surrounded.

628
00:46:11.240 --> 00:46:13.800
- What did you do?
- And, Daddy,
they took my boot!

629
00:46:13.840 --> 00:46:15.840
They took... Those are
the ones I bought you.

630
00:46:15.920 --> 00:46:17.080
And I was saved!

631
00:46:17.160 --> 00:46:21.040
I was saved by a flying
wild man in a loincloth.

632
00:46:21.080 --> 00:46:23.880
- Loincloth, good Lord.
- What is she talking about?

633
00:46:23.920 --> 00:46:27.240
I haven't the foggiest idea.
Takes after her mother,
you know.

634
00:46:27.320 --> 00:46:30.400
She'd come up with stories.
Not about men in loincloths...

635
00:46:30.480 --> 00:46:32.600
- And there were gorillas!
- Gorillas?

636
00:46:32.680 --> 00:46:33.680
They were doing...

637
00:46:33.720 --> 00:46:36.640
You saw the gorillas? Where?

638
00:46:36.720 --> 00:46:39.800
- He left with them.
- Who, dear, who?

639
00:46:40.480 --> 00:46:42.040
Tarzan.

640
00:46:42.120 --> 00:46:43.400
Tarzan?

641
00:46:43.440 --> 00:46:45.600
The ape man.

642
00:46:47.640 --> 00:46:49.240
[screeching]

643
00:46:49.280 --> 00:46:51.920
[Kerchak] Everyone.
We will avoid the strangers.

644
00:46:52.000 --> 00:46:54.520
Do not let them see you,
and do not seek them out.

645
00:46:54.560 --> 00:46:56.000
[Tarzan] They mean us no harm.

646
00:46:56.080 --> 00:46:57.680
Tarzan, I don't know them.

647
00:46:57.720 --> 00:46:59.240
I do. I've spent time
with them.

648
00:46:59.320 --> 00:47:01.920
You may be willing to risk
our safety, I'm not.

649
00:47:02.000 --> 00:47:04.720
Why are you threatened
by anyone different from you?

650
00:47:07.280 --> 00:47:12.000
Protect this family,
and stay away from them.

651
00:47:15.240 --> 00:47:17.760
Tarzan, for once,
listen to Kerchak.

652
00:47:17.840 --> 00:47:21.000
Why didn't you tell me
there were creatures
that look like me?

653
00:47:29.800 --> 00:47:32.560
[Jane] Well, he didn't
stand upright. He sort of...

654
00:47:32.720 --> 00:47:34.240
- ...crouched.
- Really?

655
00:47:34.280 --> 00:47:36.200
He supported his weight
on his knuckles.

656
00:47:36.280 --> 00:47:39.240
- On the knuckles.
- See? Exactly like a gorilla.

657
00:47:39.280 --> 00:47:42.160
- Extraordinary.
- It was amazing!

658
00:47:42.240 --> 00:47:44.200
He'd bend his
elbows out like this.

659
00:47:44.280 --> 00:47:45.600
And then he walks, like this.

660
00:47:45.680 --> 00:47:48.800
Oh, I see! Like Aunt Isabel.

661
00:47:48.880 --> 00:47:50.800
- [laughter]
- [Porter] Ba, ba, ba, ba, ba.

662
00:47:50.840 --> 00:47:52.320
- [Porter] This is capital!
- Hmm.

663
00:47:52.400 --> 00:47:54.800
Janey-Jane, what a discovery!

664
00:47:54.880 --> 00:47:57.120
A man with no language,
no human behavior...

665
00:47:57.200 --> 00:47:59.640
And no respect
for personal boundaries.

666
00:47:59.720 --> 00:48:02.040
- How do you mean?
- He was this close, Daddy.

667
00:48:02.120 --> 00:48:03.360
Staring at me.

668
00:48:03.440 --> 00:48:06.720
He seemed confused at first,

669
00:48:06.800 --> 00:48:09.360
as if he's never seen
another human before.

670
00:48:09.440 --> 00:48:14.640
And his eyes were intense
and focused, and...

671
00:48:15.680 --> 00:48:18.840
[Jane] I've never seen
such eyes.

672
00:48:21.040 --> 00:48:25.400
Oh, shall I leave you and the
blackboard alone for a moment?

673
00:48:25.480 --> 00:48:28.360
Daddy, stop it.
The point is,

674
00:48:28.440 --> 00:48:31.560
think of what we could learn
from him. We must find him.

675
00:48:31.680 --> 00:48:33.040
Oh!

676
00:48:33.120 --> 00:48:36.840
Professor, you are here
to find gorillas,

677
00:48:36.920 --> 00:48:39.520
not indulge
some girlish fantasy.

678
00:48:39.560 --> 00:48:42.280
Fantasy? I didn't imagine him.

679
00:48:42.320 --> 00:48:43.600
Tarzan is...

680
00:48:43.680 --> 00:48:46.320
- [gasps]
- ...real.

681
00:48:46.400 --> 00:48:48.920
Ah! [stammering] It's him!

682
00:48:49.000 --> 00:48:50.720
It's him, it's him. Tarzan!

683
00:48:50.800 --> 00:48:52.520
- Professor, Jane, stand back!
- Wait!

684
00:48:52.560 --> 00:48:54.680
- No!
- [gunshot]

685
00:48:54.720 --> 00:48:56.360
[Tarzan] Clayton.

686
00:48:58.520 --> 00:49:00.640
- Clayton.
- Ah! [laughing]

687
00:49:00.680 --> 00:49:03.040
Have we met?

688
00:49:04.080 --> 00:49:05.840
How does he know my name?

689
00:49:05.920 --> 00:49:08.440
He thinks it means
the sound of a gunshot.

690
00:49:08.520 --> 00:49:12.640
- Jane.
- Yes. Hello, Tarzan.

691
00:49:12.720 --> 00:49:14.960
I see what you mean
about personal boundaries.

692
00:49:15.040 --> 00:49:17.680
What's he doing?

693
00:49:18.680 --> 00:49:20.560
[Porter] Look at him, Jane.

694
00:49:20.600 --> 00:49:22.680
Moves like an ape,
but looks like a man.

695
00:49:22.720 --> 00:49:25.720
He could be the missing link.

696
00:49:25.760 --> 00:49:29.000
Or our link to the gorillas.

697
00:49:29.040 --> 00:49:30.840
Ah! Yes, yes.

698
00:49:30.880 --> 00:49:35.200
[clears throat]
Where are the gorillas?

699
00:49:36.280 --> 00:49:38.400
Go-ri-llas!

700
00:49:38.440 --> 00:49:40.400
Go-ri-llas!

701
00:49:40.440 --> 00:49:42.280
Shouting won't help,
Mr. Clayton.

702
00:49:42.360 --> 00:49:44.080
He doesn't
understand English.

703
00:49:44.120 --> 00:49:46.040
Then I'll make him understand.

704
00:49:46.080 --> 00:49:48.880
If I can teach a parrot
to sing God Save the Queen,

705
00:49:48.920 --> 00:49:52.880
I can certainly teach
this savage a thing or two.

706
00:49:53.880 --> 00:49:55.920
Gorilla.

707
00:49:57.160 --> 00:49:58.960
Gorilla.

708
00:49:59.040 --> 00:50:01.600
- [chuckles] He's got it!
- Gorilla.

709
00:50:01.680 --> 00:50:04.640
- Go-ril-la.
- Perhaps not.

710
00:50:04.720 --> 00:50:07.920
- Oh, no, no, no!
- Oh, no, no, no!

711
00:50:07.960 --> 00:50:10.520
Gimme that. Leave it.

712
00:50:10.600 --> 00:50:13.800
Mr. Clayton, I think
I'll take it from here.

