♪ I wanna know ♪♪

755
00:53:56.080 --> 00:54:00.440
Oh, Terk,
I've never seen him so happy.

756
00:54:00.480 --> 00:54:02.520
Yeah? I give it a week.

757
00:54:06.160 --> 00:54:09.160
- [man 1] Aye, cut her loose!
- [man 2] Come on,
pull it down.

758
00:54:09.240 --> 00:54:11.440
[man 3] All right,
move it, ya bilge rats!

759
00:54:11.520 --> 00:54:12.920
[man 4] Heave ho, lads.

760
00:54:13.000 --> 00:54:15.240
[man 5] Put your back in it.
All right, move it.

761
00:54:15.320 --> 00:54:18.080
[Porter] Please, don't...
I've waited 30 years for this

762
00:54:18.160 --> 00:54:20.680
and I won't leave
until I see a gorilla.

763
00:54:20.720 --> 00:54:25.000
Isn't this dreadful, Tarzan?
No! No, no, wait!

764
00:54:25.040 --> 00:54:27.280
[man 6] Pick your barrel up.
Pick it up.

765
00:54:27.360 --> 00:54:29.360
[man 7] Here we go.
Here we go.

766
00:54:29.440 --> 00:54:32.960
[Clayton] You're the captain.
Tell them you've
had engine trouble,

767
00:54:33.040 --> 00:54:34.520
and give us two more days.

768
00:54:34.600 --> 00:54:37.040
And be late at every port
from here to London?

769
00:54:37.080 --> 00:54:38.640
We'll have come for nothing.

770
00:54:38.680 --> 00:54:42.440
I'm sorry, Miss Porter,
but I simply can't do it.

771
00:54:42.520 --> 00:54:45.080
[groans] This is your fault.

772
00:54:45.160 --> 00:54:46.880
I should've
followed my instincts

773
00:54:46.960 --> 00:54:48.640
and set traps for the beasts.

774
00:54:48.720 --> 00:54:51.520
Don't you think
I'm disappointed
about the gorillas?

775
00:54:51.520 --> 00:54:54.240
You are absolutely impossible!
[gasps]

776
00:54:54.320 --> 00:54:57.880
Tarzan. I was so afraid that
you wouldn't come in time.

777
00:54:57.920 --> 00:54:59.200
The boat's arrived.

778
00:54:59.280 --> 00:55:02.400
The boat that's come
to take us home, to England.

779
00:55:02.440 --> 00:55:06.880
And Daddy and I were...
Well, I was wondering...

780
00:55:06.960 --> 00:55:10.080
Well, we really hope
that you'll come with us.

781
00:55:10.080 --> 00:55:11.560
Won't you?

782
00:55:12.760 --> 00:55:15.880
Go see England today.
Come home tomorrow.

783
00:55:15.920 --> 00:55:17.920
Oh, no.

784
00:55:18.000 --> 00:55:21.240
Well, see, it would be very
difficult to come back...

785
00:55:21.320 --> 00:55:22.560
...ever.

786
00:55:22.600 --> 00:55:24.200
Not come back?

787
00:55:24.240 --> 00:55:28.240
I know it sounds awful,
but you belong with us,
with people.

788
00:55:28.320 --> 00:55:30.280
Jane must stay with Tarzan.

789
00:55:30.360 --> 00:55:33.720
Stay here? Oh, no, no, no...
My laundry.

790
00:55:33.760 --> 00:55:37.240
No, I can't stay.
Look, I've got...

791
00:55:37.280 --> 00:55:39.720
I'm with my father, and...

792
00:55:39.760 --> 00:55:43.520
Jane... stay.

793
00:55:43.600 --> 00:55:45.880
- But...
- Please.

794
00:55:48.320 --> 00:55:50.800
But, I can't.

795
00:55:50.880 --> 00:55:53.160
[sobbing]

796
00:55:53.240 --> 00:55:55.240
[Clayton] Women.
[chuckles]

797
00:55:55.280 --> 00:55:58.120
How typical.
Thank you, Jones.

798
00:55:58.160 --> 00:56:02.200
Even if you hadn't grown up
a savage, you'd be lost.

799
00:56:02.280 --> 00:56:05.760
There are no trails
through a woman's heart.

800
00:56:05.840 --> 00:56:09.400
- Jane is going.
- Yes.

801
00:56:09.440 --> 00:56:13.600
If only she could've spent
more time with the gorillas.

802
00:56:13.640 --> 00:56:15.960
She's so disappointed.

803
00:56:16.000 --> 00:56:18.800
Crushed, really.

804
00:56:18.880 --> 00:56:21.880
Sorry, old boy.

805
00:56:21.960 --> 00:56:25.360
Oh, well, I'd best get
Jane's things to the ship.

806
00:56:29.560 --> 00:56:30.640
Clayton.

807
00:56:33.120 --> 00:56:36.400
If Jane sees gorillas,
she stays?

808
00:56:36.480 --> 00:56:40.200
Say, that's why she came,
isn't it?

809
00:56:42.360 --> 00:56:45.000
- I'll do it.
- Good man!

810
00:56:45.040 --> 00:56:46.560
- Snipes?
- Sir?

811
00:56:46.640 --> 00:56:51.320
Get the boys together. There's
gonna be a change in plans.

812
00:56:51.400 --> 00:56:53.400
Terk, just get
Kerchak out of the way.

813
00:56:53.480 --> 00:56:55.440
- What?
- I'd be happy to get...

814
00:56:55.480 --> 00:56:59.120
Hey! Shut your trunk
and get me out of here.

815
00:56:59.160 --> 00:57:01.520
[Terk]
Can you believe that guy?

816
00:57:01.560 --> 00:57:05.000
Drops us like a newborn
giraffe, kerplop!

817
00:57:05.040 --> 00:57:08.520
Now waltzes in here
and expects us to just...

818
00:57:08.600 --> 00:57:11.200
Terk, I'm asking you
as a friend.

819
00:57:11.320 --> 00:57:13.840
[groans]

820
00:57:13.920 --> 00:57:16.720
With the face and the eyes
and the...

821
00:57:16.800 --> 00:57:21.360
All right! But don't make me
do anything embarrassing.

822
00:57:22.160 --> 00:57:24.080
I'm gonna kill him!!

823
00:57:24.160 --> 00:57:27.480
I thought that dress
was rather slimming on you.

824
00:57:27.520 --> 00:57:30.400
Really? I thought it was
a little revealing
and kind of...

825
00:57:30.480 --> 00:57:32.360
- [loud roar]
- [screaming]

826
00:57:33.680 --> 00:57:35.880
How does she move
in this thing?

827
00:57:39.280 --> 00:57:41.280
[Terk] Look out!

828
00:58:06.720 --> 00:58:09.840
- Look, Daddy!
- [stammering] Where?

829
00:58:09.920 --> 00:58:12.920
Jane. [panting]

830
00:58:13.000 --> 00:58:15.360
[Clayton] Now, be careful,
professor.

831
00:58:15.400 --> 00:58:17.200
[Porter] Mustn't,
mustn't frighten.

832
00:58:17.240 --> 00:58:20.480
She's beautiful.

833
00:58:20.600 --> 00:58:22.720
She's my mother.

834
00:58:22.760 --> 00:58:26.120
But... This is your...

835
00:58:27.440 --> 00:58:29.120
...mother?

836
00:58:33.200 --> 00:58:35.320
[soft hooting]

837
00:58:38.760 --> 00:58:41.920
- [stammering]
What's happening?
- I don't know, Daddy.

838
00:58:42.000 --> 00:58:44.120
Oh! It's getting away!

839
00:58:44.160 --> 00:58:46.720
No! You'll only
frighten her more.

840
00:58:50.880 --> 00:58:52.880
[hooting]

841
00:58:54.280 --> 00:58:58.120
Yes, absolutely, my dear.
Good idea.

842
00:58:58.200 --> 00:59:00.360
What are you doing?
Want to frighten them?

843
00:59:00.440 --> 00:59:02.600
Get up. Get...

844
00:59:02.640 --> 00:59:04.920
Don't get up.

845
00:59:26.120 --> 00:59:29.160
[stammering] Oh!

846
00:59:32.080 --> 00:59:33.840
[grunting]

847
00:59:36.080 --> 00:59:37.320
Hello.

848
00:59:42.320 --> 00:59:44.840
It's very nice
to meet you, too.

849
00:59:48.800 --> 00:59:52.200
Oh, Your Majesty,
you're such a tease.

850
00:59:52.320 --> 00:59:55.080
Whoa! Hello. Hello.

851
00:59:55.160 --> 00:59:58.240
Archimedes Q. Porter
at your service.

852
00:59:58.320 --> 01:00:00.840
Quite a grip you've got.

853
01:00:00.920 --> 01:00:04.160
Oh, thank you, yes.
Is that one of mine?

854
01:00:05.760 --> 01:00:07.640
This is wonderful,
Mr. Clayton!

855
01:00:07.680 --> 01:00:09.360
Look, look! Social grooming.

856
01:00:09.440 --> 01:00:12.640
Congratulations, professor.

857
01:00:12.680 --> 01:00:15.960
Our dream has come true.

858
01:00:19.800 --> 01:00:21.200
Give me that!

859
01:00:21.240 --> 01:00:23.720
Hey, what are you doing?
Now, stop that! Stop!

860
01:00:23.760 --> 01:00:25.360
Hold on now. Leave that!

861
01:00:25.440 --> 01:00:27.640
That is not to be played with!

862
01:00:42.440 --> 01:00:43.880
Can you teach me?

863
01:00:43.920 --> 01:00:47.240
- Speak gorilla?
- Hmm. Yes.

864
01:00:49.080 --> 01:00:51.960
[Tarzan grunts,
Jane repeats]

865
01:01:08.720 --> 01:01:12.160
Good heavens, what did I say?

866
01:01:12.240 --> 01:01:15.440
That Jane stays with Tarzan.

867
01:01:15.480 --> 01:01:18.920
Stay? But I...
I thought we'd already...

868
01:01:18.960 --> 01:01:21.640
- Tarzan, I...
- [Terk] Whoa!

869
01:01:26.320 --> 01:01:29.320
- Is that my dress?
- Oh, no.

870
01:01:29.400 --> 01:01:31.080
[roaring]

871
01:01:33.320 --> 01:01:34.360
[Jane] Daddy.

872
01:01:37.920 --> 01:01:39.760
Give it to me!

873
01:01:42.920 --> 01:01:43.920
Go!

874
01:02:02.400 --> 01:02:03.480
Go!

875
01:02:05.200 --> 01:02:07.040
Wait, wait! Tarzan!

876
01:02:07.160 --> 01:02:08.320
Go now!

877
01:02:08.360 --> 01:02:11.640
Jane, quickly! Hurry!
Come along!

878
01:02:18.040 --> 01:02:20.280
[both panting]

879
01:02:30.840 --> 01:02:34.840
Kerchak, I didn't...
I'm sorry, I...

880
01:02:34.920 --> 01:02:38.520
I asked you
to protect our family.

881
01:02:38.560 --> 01:02:41.680
And you betrayed us all.

882
01:03:10.040 --> 01:03:12.200
I'm so confused.

883
01:03:14.760 --> 01:03:16.400
Come with me.

884
01:03:16.400 --> 01:03:19.760
There's something I should've
shown you long ago.

885
01:04:15.400 --> 01:04:16.960
[glass breaking]

886
01:04:39.640 --> 01:04:41.480
Is this me?

887
01:04:45.680 --> 01:04:47.760
And this is my father,

888
01:04:47.800 --> 01:04:49.360
and...

889
01:04:49.440 --> 01:04:51.240
and my...

890
01:04:52.800 --> 01:04:54.800
Now you know.

891
01:04:54.840 --> 01:04:59.240
Tarzan, I just want you
to be happy,

892
01:04:59.320 --> 01:05:02.040
whatever you decide.

893
01:05:49.520 --> 01:05:53.720
No matter where I go,
you will always be my mother.

894
01:05:53.800 --> 01:05:56.040
[sobbing]

895
01:05:58.200 --> 01:06:01.720
And you will always be
in my heart.

896
01:06:21.320 --> 01:06:23.800
Goodbye, Tarzan.

897
01:06:23.920 --> 01:06:26.080
- [Jane] Tarzan!
- [men shouting]

898
01:06:26.160 --> 01:06:28.200
I'm so glad you
found us in time.

899
01:06:37.600 --> 01:06:39.400
Tarzan!

900
01:06:39.440 --> 01:06:42.480
We're too late!
I can't believe it!

901
01:06:42.560 --> 01:06:44.680
If you had pulled over
and asked for directions...

902
01:06:44.760 --> 01:06:46.800
We didn't get to say goodbye.

903
01:06:46.880 --> 01:06:50.240
Well, good riddance,
all right?
Who needs you, huh?

904
01:06:50.360 --> 01:06:52.400
Go on, get out of here,
bald boy!

905
01:06:52.440 --> 01:06:55.320
You, you ingrate!
You bald ingrate!

906
01:06:55.400 --> 01:06:57.400
Go on and rot, for all I care!

907
01:06:57.440 --> 01:06:59.160
Go!

908
01:07:01.280 --> 01:07:03.240
What are you looking at?

909
01:07:03.280 --> 01:07:05.200
I'm gonna miss him, too.

910
01:07:13.440 --> 01:07:16.560
[Jane] Tarzan,
you can't imagine
what's in store for you.

911
01:07:16.640 --> 01:07:17.920
You'll see the world.

912
01:07:17.960 --> 01:07:19.720
Everyone's going
to want to meet you.

913
01:07:19.800 --> 01:07:21.960
Kings, scientists,
famous writers.

914
01:07:22.040 --> 01:07:25.320
Yes. Darwin and Kipling.
Queen Victoria!

915
01:07:25.440 --> 01:07:27.720
I haven't met her,
but I heard she's nice.

916
01:07:27.800 --> 01:07:29.440
And I'll be with Jane?

917
01:07:31.640 --> 01:07:34.360
Yes, with Jane.
[chuckles]

918
01:07:35.320 --> 01:07:37.600
Oh! Slippery.

919
01:07:57.040 --> 01:07:59.800
- [sinister laughing]
- [Jane] Tarzan!

920
01:07:59.840 --> 01:08:02.120
- Ow!
- Tarzan!

921
01:08:02.160 --> 01:08:03.600
[man] Get him!

922
01:08:09.720 --> 01:08:11.800
- [Jane] Tarzan!
- [Tarzan] Jane!

923
01:08:29.160 --> 01:08:32.200
- [struggling]
- [gunshot]

924
01:08:32.240 --> 01:08:34.040
What's going on here?

925
01:08:34.080 --> 01:08:36.400
Clayton! Clayton, help!

926
01:08:38.200 --> 01:08:40.080
Have we met?

927
01:08:43.440 --> 01:08:47.240
Ah, yes, the ape man.

928
01:08:47.920 --> 01:08:50.400
Clayton, you...

929
01:08:50.520 --> 01:08:51.560
You...

930
01:08:53.200 --> 01:08:55.760
So sorry about the rude
welcome, old boy,

931
01:08:55.840 --> 01:08:57.880
but I couldn't have you
making a scene

932
01:08:57.920 --> 01:09:02.040
when we put your furry friends
in their cages.

933
01:09:02.160 --> 01:09:03.640
Why?

934
01:09:04.240 --> 01:09:05.400
Why?

935
01:09:05.440 --> 01:09:08.240
For three hundred pounds
sterling a head.

936
01:09:08.280 --> 01:09:11.720
Actually, I have you
to thank, my boy.

937
01:09:11.800 --> 01:09:14.880
Couldn't have done it
without you.

938
01:09:17.040 --> 01:09:19.240
Lock him up with the others.

939
01:09:20.440 --> 01:09:22.280
No!

940
01:09:23.960 --> 01:09:25.640
That sounded like Tarzan.

941
01:09:25.720 --> 01:09:28.040
He sounded like
he was in trouble.

942
01:09:28.080 --> 01:09:30.120
Yeah, well, why doesn't
he get his new friends

943
01:09:30.200 --> 01:09:31.680
to help him?
I don't care.

944
01:09:32.880 --> 01:09:35.080
That's it!

945
01:09:35.160 --> 01:09:38.240
I've had it with you
and your emotional
constipation!

946
01:09:38.360 --> 01:09:41.280
Tarzan needs us
and we're gonna help him!

947
01:09:41.320 --> 01:09:45.400
You got that? Now, pipe down
and hang on tight!

948
01:09:45.440 --> 01:09:47.600
We've got a boat to catch.

949
01:09:47.680 --> 01:09:50.000
[bugle call]

950
01:09:56.320 --> 01:09:59.920
[sputtering, coughing]
I've never felt so alive!

951
01:09:59.960 --> 01:10:02.720
Good! 'Cause I'm
gonna kill you!

952
01:10:02.800 --> 01:10:04.960
No time for that now, missy.

953
01:10:15.120 --> 01:10:17.360
[radar pings]

954
01:10:19.200 --> 01:10:20.920
[shouting]

955
01:10:25.320 --> 01:10:27.440
Tarzan, it's no use. Don't!

956
01:10:36.000 --> 01:10:38.960
- Clayton.
- Yes, Clayton.

957
01:10:39.000 --> 01:10:43.160
Clayton betrayed us all.
I'm so sorry, Tarzan.

958
01:10:43.240 --> 01:10:45.920
No, I did this.

959
01:10:46.000 --> 01:10:50.480
I betrayed my family.
Kerchak was right.

960
01:10:50.560 --> 01:10:55.360
Those magnificent creatures,
shivering in cages.

961
01:10:55.480 --> 01:10:58.320
What is this world coming to?

962
01:11:03.840 --> 01:11:06.520
Oh, by Jove!
Don't know my own strength.

963
01:11:08.840 --> 01:11:10.680
[shouting]

964
01:11:11.520 --> 01:11:13.040
What was that?

965
01:11:13.120 --> 01:11:16.000
- [Terk] You are an animal!
- [trumpets]

966
01:11:17.560 --> 01:11:19.520
That sounded
just like an elephant.

967
01:11:19.560 --> 01:11:20.800
Tantor!

968
01:11:22.520 --> 01:11:23.600
Thanks, guys.

969
01:11:23.680 --> 01:11:26.560
I thought I would never
see you again!

970
01:11:26.640 --> 01:11:29.000
And here you are.

971
01:11:29.040 --> 01:11:32.320
Sometimes you embarrass me.

972
01:11:43.000 --> 01:11:45.880
[sniffs, grunts]

973
01:11:58.880 --> 01:12:01.240
[men shouting]

974
01:12:39.720 --> 01:12:42.880
Ah! I remember you.

975
01:12:44.480 --> 01:12:47.120
I think this one
will be better off stuffed.

976
01:12:49.240 --> 01:12:51.880
[Tarzan yelling]

977
01:13:09.120 --> 01:13:10.840
You came back.

978
01:13:10.920 --> 01:13:12.480
I came home.

979
01:13:24.360 --> 01:13:25.640
[evil laugh]

980
01:13:27.480 --> 01:13:29.280
Fire!

981
01:13:35.360 --> 01:13:37.800
You there! Take what you can
back to the boat.

982
01:13:37.840 --> 01:13:39.160
Aye, aye, sir.

983
01:13:41.600 --> 01:13:44.040
I've got some hunting to do.

984
01:14:04.880 --> 01:14:07.360
[frantic hooting]

985
01:14:08.360 --> 01:14:09.560
Don't worry.

986
01:14:09.640 --> 01:14:12.080
I'm going to have you
out of this in a second.

987
01:14:16.880 --> 01:14:18.920
This should do the trick.

988
01:14:23.440 --> 01:14:24.880
[gunshot]

989
01:14:24.920 --> 01:14:27.040
- [gasps]
- [grunts]

990
01:14:36.800 --> 01:14:39.040
No!

991
01:14:40.880 --> 01:14:42.040
[gunshots]

992
01:14:42.080 --> 01:14:43.840
[Clayton] Hiding, are we?

993
01:14:43.920 --> 01:14:46.320
- Good!
- Clayton, you...

994
01:14:46.400 --> 01:14:49.760
I could use a challenge.
Because after
I get rid of you,

995
01:14:49.880 --> 01:14:55.000
rounding up your little ape
family will be all too easy!

996
01:15:01.720 --> 01:15:03.280
[thunder rumbling]

997
01:15:21.600 --> 01:15:23.520
Go ahead, shoot me.

998
01:15:24.960 --> 01:15:27.320
[Clayton laughs]

999
01:15:27.400 --> 01:15:28.960
Be a man.

1000
01:15:32.360 --> 01:15:35.280
[gunshot]

1001
01:15:35.360 --> 01:15:36.920
[panting]

1002
01:15:36.960 --> 01:15:38.640
Not a man like you!

1003
01:16:12.000 --> 01:16:13.640
Clayton, don't!

1004
01:17:02.560 --> 01:17:04.920
[labored breathing]

1005
01:17:05.840 --> 01:17:07.600
Tarzan.

1006
01:17:07.680 --> 01:17:10.800
Kerchak, forgive me.

1007
01:17:11.920 --> 01:17:13.240
No.

1008
01:17:13.360 --> 01:17:17.080
Forgive me
for not understanding

1009
01:17:17.160 --> 01:17:21.480
that you have always
been one of us.

1010
01:17:23.120 --> 01:17:26.480
[Kerchak] Our family
will look to you now.

1011
